verbose_text: Hepatic serotonin levels increased insignificantly in Con A treated vs. vehicle and mirtazapine treated mice; however, mirtazapine treatment in Con A treated mice significantly increased hepatic serotonin levels, compared to both control groups (hepatic serotonin levels [pg/mg protein]; vehicle : 127.2 +/-17.2 vs. mirtazapine treated : 119.0 +/- 12.2 vs. Con A : 157.0 +/- 11.3 vs. Con A + mirtazapine : * 192.6 +/- 23.1; * p < 0.05 vs. vehicle and mirtazapine groups; n = 4-5 mice per group).
evidence: serotonin levels increased insignificantly in Con A
